# Smooth UX — Transitions & Visual Feedback

Every interactive element MUST have smooth transitions, hover states, and visual feedback. No abrupt changes.

## Transitions via Tailwind

EVERY property change MUST be animated. Use Tailwind transition utilities:

```scss
.item {
  @apply transition-all duration-200 ease-in-out;
}
```

For specific properties only:

```scss
.item { @apply transition-opacity duration-200 ease-in-out; }
.item { @apply transition-colors duration-200 ease-in-out; }
.item { @apply transition-transform duration-200 ease-in-out; }
```

## Hover States are Mandatory

Every clickable element MUST have a `:hover` state:

```scss
.item {
  @apply opacity-70;
  color: var(--primer-fg-on-emphasis);
}

.item:hover {
  @apply opacity-100;
}
```

For buttons on dark backgrounds, use `filter: brightness()` for hover feedback:

```scss
.button.button {
  background-color: var(--primer-neutral-muted);

  &:hover {
    background-color: var(--primer-neutral-muted);
    filter: brightness(0.5);
  }
}
```

## Active/Pressed Feedback

Interactive elements SHOULD have `:active` with subtle scale:

```scss
.item:active {
  @apply scale-95;
}
```

## What is FORBIDDEN

```scss
// FORBIDDEN — raw CSS transitions
.item { transition: opacity 200ms ease; }
.item { transition: color var(--duration) var(--easing); }

// FORBIDDEN — raw CSS values for animated properties
.item { opacity: 0.7; }
.item:active { transform: scale(0.95); }

// REQUIRED — Tailwind utilities
.item { @apply opacity-70 transition-all duration-200 ease-in-out; }
.item:active { @apply scale-95; }
```
